                        xml:lang="en">Anglesey</p>
                  </cell>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.075in; padding-right: 0.075in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">7 Jul. Cycad, Casuar, Laurin Polygon, Santal.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                           <p rend="Footnote"
                              style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                              xml:lang="en">
                              <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                              <seg style="">
                                 <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                              </seg>
                              <name key="Cycadeae">Cycadeae</name>, <name key="Casuarineae">Casuarineae</name>, <name key="Laurineae">Laurineae</name>, <name key="Polygonaceae">Polygonaceae</name>, <name key="Santalaceae">Santalaceae</name>.</p>
                        </note>
                     </p>
                  </cell>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.075in; padding-right: 0.075in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">1 <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>-</p>
                  </cell>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.075in; padding-right: 0.075in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">- True Britain<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                           <p rend="Footnote"
                              style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                              xml:lang="en">
                              <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                              <seg style="">
                                 <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                              </seg>i.e. <seg style="font-style: italic; ">True Briton</seg>.</p>
                        </note>
                     </p>
                  </cell>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.075in; padding-right: 0.075in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">24 Oct miscell. <name key="Proteaceae">Proteaceae</name> (small genera)</p>
                  </cell>
               </row>
            </table>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Genera <name key="Isopogon">Isopogon</name> &amp; <name key="Petrophila">Petrophila</name> will give me some trouble, as I have either to unite them or what will be of less advantage, to remodel them.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The letter ends, without valediction, with about 20% of the sheet left blank. M maintained both genera, B68.12.02, summarizing their cardinal characters on p. 246.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
